<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="591" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d591">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5504: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-28"><hi rend="italic">October 28,
                                1919</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received October 28, 10:45
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>[From <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName>:]</p>
                        <p>447. October 28th, 4 p.m. Am informed that <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> has just recalled <persName>Rozanoff</persName>
                            from Vladivostok to Omsk to explain himself. This probably means
                            definite elimination of <persName>Rozanoff</persName> from Far East
                            situation. <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName>.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tenney</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>